The paper discusses the use of robotics to study the movement of slime mould, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of automated guidance and control mechanisms, which suggests that it may also fall under the multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories. The use of attractant and repellent stimuli to guide the movement of the swarm suggests that the paper may also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
